What is a Multiplex Network?

A multiplex is a multi-layer network:

Layer 1: Streets - Road network (edges = road segments)
Layer 2: TAZ - Traffic Analysis Zones
Layer 3: OD Flows - Origin-Destination connections

Taxi trips traverse Layer 1 (streets), triggering flows between zones (Layer 2-3).

How Taxi Trips Work on Multiplex:
1. GPS trajectory recorded
2. Map-matched to street edges
3. Each edge has FC from traffic flow model
4. Trip FC = sum of edge FCs
5. This aggregates to zone-level (TAZ layer)
